{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-js","path":"/articles/march-listening/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"SuperCoolNeato"}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Travel Headphone Gear\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/885cf285bdcc9504df7ccc429bd23637/4b190/IMG_0881.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/885cf285bdcc9504df7ccc429bd23637/e07e9/IMG_0881.jpg 200w,\n/static/885cf285bdcc9504df7ccc429bd23637/066f9/IMG_0881.jpg 400w,\n/static/885cf285bdcc9504df7ccc429bd23637/4b190/IMG_0881.jpg 800w,\n/static/885cf285bdcc9504df7ccc429bd23637/e5166/IMG_0881.jpg 1200w,\n/static/885cf285bdcc9504df7ccc429bd23637/b17f8/IMG_0881.jpg 1600w,\n/static/885cf285bdcc9504df7ccc429bd23637/d2602/IMG_0881.jpg 4032w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>I've been in Austin part of this month and listening through my travel headphone rig: the amazing <a href=\"http://www.theaudiophileworld.net/2012/04/sennheiser-hd380-professional-review.html\">Sennheiser HD 380 Pros</a> paired with my trusty old <a href=\"http://www.whathifi.com/audioengine/d1/review\">Audioengine D1</a>.</p>\n<p>The lightweight and noise isolating nature of the HD 380 Pros is why I favor them for long days working from coffee shops. As an added bonus that they come with a case that the 'phones fold flat into and fits nicely in my computer bag.</p>\n<p>My favorite feature of the D1 is its volume pot. Digital stepped up volume controls on computers tend to bother me. I want to control my volume in a more tangible way.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://itun.es/us/3aNFP\">Ane Brun - Songs 2003-2013</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://itun.es/us/eRGGl\">Jeff Buckly - Grace</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://itun.es/us/JX5B\">Portishead - Roseland NYC</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://itun.es/us/j0AuA\">Port O'Brien - Threadbare</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://itun.es/us/ErTcab\">The Avalaches - Since I Left You</a></p>","excerpt":"I've been in Austin part of this month and listening through my travel headphone rig: the amazing Sennheiser HD 380 Pros paired with my trusty old Audioengine D1. The lightweight and noise isolating…","frontmatter":{"title":"March Listening","date":"2016-03-18 15:00","summary":null,"author":"mimiflynn"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"8fb25e77-b320-51c2-a0e1-ff93f464d979","slug":"articles/march-listening"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1714866707"],"slicesMap":{}}